---
import "../styles/before.css";
---

<section class="before-after-section">
    <div class="before-after-grid">
        <!-- LEFT: BEFORE MONOLITHIC -->
        <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">
                <span class="panel-label">BEFORE: MONOLITHIC</span>
                <span class="badge badge--risk">High Risk</span>
            </div>

            <div class="die-visual">
                <span class="die-x">✕</span>
                <span class="die-dot"></span>
            </div>

            <div class="stats">
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Silicon Area</span>
                    <span class="stat-value">800mm²</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Defects</span>
                    <span class="stat-value stat-value--danger"
                        >1 Particle</span
                    >
                </div>
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Net Functional Yield</span>
                    <span class="stat-value stat-value--danger"
                        >0% (Scrap)</span
                    >
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: AFTER CHIPLETS -->
        <div class="panel">
            <div class="panel-header">
                <span class="panel-label">AFTER: CHIPLETS</span>
                <span class="badge badge--yield">High Yield</span>
            </div>

            <div class="chiplet-grid">
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip chip--defective"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
                <div class="chip"></div>
            </div>

            <div class="stats">
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Silicon Area</span>
                    <span class="stat-value">16 x 50mm²</span>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Defects</span>
                    <span class="stat-value stat-value--danger"
                        >1 Particle</span
                    >
                </div>
                <div class="stat-row">
                    <span class="stat-key">Net Functional Yield</span>
                    <span class="stat-value stat-value--success"
                        >93.75% (15/16 Kept)</span
                    >
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation">
        <p>
            The numbers above tell the whole story. A single 800mm² monolithic 
            die has nowhere to hide a defect; one particle anywhere on the silicon 
            scraps the entire chip, dropping yield to 0%. Chiplets change the math 
            entirely: by splitting the same functional area into 16 smaller, independently 
            fabricated dies, a single defect only takes out the one chiplet it lands on. 
            The other 15 are still perfectly usable, pushing the net functional yield up 
            to 93.75%.
        </p>
        <p>
            This is the core economic insight behind AMD's chiplet strategy. 
            Smaller dies are dramatically cheaper to manufacture at high yield 
            because defect probability scales with area; cut the area, and you 
            cut your exposure to the random particle that would have. 
            Otherwise, it would have ruined the whole part.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>